COMMAND TO BUILD DOCKER IMAGE
docker build -t server .

COMMAND TO RUN DOCKER CONTAINER
docker run <option> -p 80:80 -p 443:443 server

option :
--env AUTO_INDEX=OFF #TO SET OFF AUTOINDEX FROM LOCALHOST NGINX CONF 
-ti #TO SET INTERACT MODE
-p 80:80 #TO EXPOSE HOST PORT 80 TO CONTAINER PORT 80, LISTEN TO HTTP
-p 443:443 #TO EXPOSE HOST PORT 443 TO CONTAINER PORT 443, LISTEN TO HTPPS

IF RUN CONTAINER WITH INTERACT MODE / NEED TO LAUNCH BASH SCRIPT TO INITIALIZE THE SERVER
OTHERWISE, TAIL -F WILL CREATE INFINITE LOOP INTO BLACK HOLE /DEV/NULL AND MAINTAINING THE SERVER ONLINE
